{{Short description|Japanese history text completed in 879}} {{italic title}} {{Nihongo|'''''Nihon Montoku Tennō Jitsuroku'''''|日本文徳天皇実録||"The True History of Emperor Montoku of Japan"}}, abbreviated as '''Montoku Jitsuroku''', is an officially commissioned [[:en:History of Japan|Japanese history]] text. Completed in 879, it is the fifth text in the [[Rikkokushi|Six National Histories]] series. It covers the years 850-858, the years of reign of the 55th Japanese sovereign, [[:en:Emperor Montoku|Emperor Montoku]] (827-858).
==Background==
Following the earlier national history ''[[Shoku Nihon Kōki]]'' (869), in 871 [[:en:Emperor Seiwa|Emperor Seiwa]] ordered the compilation of the years since then. It was primarily edited by [[:en:Fujiwara no Mototsune|Fujiwara no Mototsune]] with assistance from [[Minabuchi no Toshina]], [[:en:Ōe no Otondo|Ōe no Otondo]], [[Shimada no Tadaomi]], [[Sugawara no Koreyoshi]], [[Yoshibuchi no Yoshinari]], and significant contributions by [[Miyako no Yoshika]].<ref name="Nihon Koten Bungaku Daijiten">Nihon Koten Bungaku Daijiten (1986:1418)</ref> The text was completed in 879.
==Contents==
Written in {{lang|ja-latn|[[:en:Kanbun|Kanbun]]|italic=no}}-style and contained within ten volumes, the contents cover nine years of [[:en:Emperor Montoku|Emperor Montoku's]] reign spanning from 850 through 858. The text is characteristic in that it contains few political details but many obituaries for nobles.<ref name="Nihon Koten Bungaku Daijiten" /><ref name="Nihon Koten Bungaku Jiten">Nihon Koten Bungaku Jiten (2007:348)</ref>
==See also==
* ''[[Ruijū Kokushi]]'', a categorized and chronological history text of the ''Six National Histories''
==External links== *[http://www.j-texts.com/chuko/montoku.html Text of the ''Nihon Montoku Tennō Jitsuroku''] (Japanese) *Manuscript [http://archive.wul.waseda.ac.jp/kosho/ri05/ri05_02450/ri05_02450_0043/ scans], [[Waseda University Library]]
